For many years experts have used responder's 2@S rebid in this auction to suggest a "stronger way to raise diamonds" than a direct 3@D raise. This makes good sense since the 2@S bid is normally idle - responder cannot have long spades or he would have bid 1@S over 1@H. On this particular hand 4@D would be a reasonable altnerative to 2@S, but it is dangerous to go above 3NT (especially playing ^*B2/1 Game Force^*N where opener could be 3532).

|at|Using responder's 2@S rebid here as a strong diamond raise has become very popular, but most partnerships are not getting very good mileage out of this bid. Here is what we suggest:

