The same general idea works when opener's rebid is 2@C instead of 2@D:

|cs|1|ht|d|at|^-{|ia|1hp1np2cp!2sp!2np?|at|}
^-
The main difference here is that responder does not need the 2@S bid to differentiate ^*Igood hands^*N with long diamonds from ^*ibad hands^*N with long diamonds. Responder can simply bid 2@D over 2@C as an attempt to sign off in diamonds and jump to 3@D to suggest long diamonds and a maximum for 1NT.

When the opening bid is 1@S (rather than 1@H) these auctions become much more difficult for responder. It is possible to use various relays in these auctions as well, but only at the expense of some useful natural bids. If the response to this week's presentation is favorable then we will consider publishing more articles along these lines in future ^*BDeals of the Week^*N.

